s—such as excessive leverage, overconfidence, mania, and panic in speculative markets—and Kenneth J. Arrow and Joseph E. Stiglitz contextualize Scheinkman's findings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCapital marketxHistory. 0aInvestmentsxHistory. 0aSpeculationxHistory. 0aStocksxPricesxHistory. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aArrow, Kenneth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArrow, Kenneth.1 aBolton, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolton, Patrick.1 aGrossman, Sanford J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrossman, Sanford.1 aScheinkman, José A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStiglitz, Joseph E.1 aStiglitz, Joseph E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP Single-User eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070982708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/sche1590240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231537636423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231537636/original  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-070982-7  CUP Single-User eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles